defs.name: Range
defs.docs: An iterator over the range [start, stop)

defs.name: range
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator over the given range [start, stop) (that is, starting
 at start (inclusive), and ending at stop (exclusive)).

defs.name: next_back
defs.docs:
`Integer` is required to ensure the range will be the same regardless of
 the direction it is consumed.

defs.name: RangeInclusive
defs.docs: An iterator over the range [start, stop]

defs.name: range_inclusive
defs.docs: Return an iterator over the range [start, stop]

defs.name: RangeStep
defs.docs: An iterator over the range [start, stop) by `step`. It handles overflow by stopping.

defs.name: range_step
